00:16:15,790 --> 00:16:18,980
Please keep this interview
confidential with MSC News only.

266
00:16:19,350 --> 00:16:21,470
Please don't give an interview
to other reporters, okay?

267
00:16:21,560 --> 00:16:22,960
Sure, I can do that.

268
00:16:24,060 --> 00:16:24,900
Come with me!

269
00:16:26,410 --> 00:16:27,930
Sorry, but it's over.

270
00:16:28,130 --> 00:16:29,530
Seonbae, let's wrap it up.

271
00:16:30,330 --> 00:16:31,940
Don't tell this person anything.

272
00:16:32,030 --> 00:16:33,740
I'll be in touch again soon.

273
00:16:34,060 --> 00:16:34,960
I said, come with me!

274
00:16:35,360 --> 00:16:36,230
Dal-Po...

275
00:16:37,060 --> 00:16:38,470
I'm sorry, but it's urgent.

276
00:16:51,810 --> 00:16:52,810
Dal-Po.

277
00:16:53,910 --> 00:16:54,910
Choi Dal-Po.

278
00:16:57,800 --> 00:16:58,800
Hey, what's wrong with you?

279
00:16:58,890 --> 00:17:00,820
Are you trying to ruin my exclusive news?

280
00:17:04,030 --> 00:17:05,440
Don't get in touch with that man.

281
00:17:05,530 --> 00:17:08,070
That man is very dangerous.
He extremely hates reporters.

282
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:09,340
I know.

283
00:17:09,430 --> 00:17:11,374
I heard the story, and he has
the reason to hate them.

284
00:17:12,310 --> 00:17:13,570
Do you remember the story of...

285
00:17:13,660 --> 00:17:16,201
the fireman who's skeletal remains
found during our interview at YGN?

286
00:17:16,500 --> 00:17:18,280
He said he's the son of that fireman.

287
00:17:18,370 --> 00:17:19,921
Of course he'd hate reporters.

288
00:17:20,220 --> 00:17:21,650
I'd really hate them too if I were him.

289
00:17:21,740 --> 00:17:23,410
That's why he's dangerous to you...

290
00:17:25,330 --> 00:17:28,040
I mean, you don't know
what he'd do to reporters, so...

291
00:17:28,130 --> 00:17:31,220
That man put his life on the
line to save the life of another.

292
00:17:31,310 --> 00:17:32,977
A man like that would never harm anyone.

293
00:17:34,750 --> 00:17:35,600
I know.

294
00:17:35,810 --> 00:17:37,114
I know that man...

295
00:17:37,550 --> 00:17:38,400
and he's dangerous.

296
00:17:38,850 --> 00:17:41,991
So have someone else do his
interviews, and you stay out of it.

297
00:17:42,260 --> 00:17:43,510
Why only me to stay out of it?

298
00:17:43,620 --> 00:17:44,900
Am I the only one in danger?

299
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:49,070
Don't tell me to just stay out of it, and
explain it to me so that I can understand.

300
00:17:51,380 --> 00:17:53,050
Can't I... just be that reason?

301
00:17:54,840 --> 00:17:55,890
Because it's me...

302
00:17:56,500 --> 00:17:57,530
Because it's my word...

303
00:17:59,340 --> 00:18:01,710
Because you know that I care
for you more than anyone else.

304
00:18:01,810 --> 00:18:03,200
Can't you just trust me?

305
00:18:07,550 --> 00:18:08,420
Dal-Po...

306
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:09,720
Please.

307
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:15,890
Please don't get involved with that man.

308
00:18:16,480 --> 00:18:18,170
Don't ask me for reasons. Just please...

309
00:18:19,600 --> 00:18:21,210
Please just do this for me, okay?

310
00:18:26,590 --> 00:18:27,430
You...

311
00:18:28,080 --> 00:18:29,940
You know something that
I don't, don't you?

312
00:18:31,910 --> 00:18:32,750
Yeah.

313
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:35,390
You won't tell me even
if I ask, will you?

314
00:18:37,980 --> 00:18:38,900
I can't.

315
00:18:41,440 --> 00:18:42,900
It's for my own sake, isn't it?

316
00:18:47,140 --> 00:18:47,980
Yeah.

317
00:18:51,540 --> 00:18:52,440
Okay.

318
00:18:53,150 --> 00:18:54,060
I'll do as you say.

319
00:18:55,470 --> 00:18:58,140
I have so many things to ask
right now, but I won't.

320
00:18:59,160 --> 00:19:01,390
I can't do anything about the
interview I just had from airing,

321
00:19:01,480 --> 00:19:02,720
but I won't do any more of it.

322
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:05,340
Because I trust you
more than I trust him.

323
00:19:08,580 --> 00:19:09,710
You're being serious, right?

324
00:19:10,790 --> 00:19:11,790
I'm serious.

325
00:19:12,220 --> 00:19:13,890
See? I'm not hiccuping.

326
00:19:24,180 --> 00:19:25,804
You know that as a Pinocchio,

327
00:19:25,895 --> 00:19:27,805
I can only make promises that I can keep.

328
00:19:28,930 --> 00:19:30,180
So you can trust me.

329
00:19:30,680 --> 00:19:33,460
I will never do anything
that'll cause you to worry.

330
00:19:35,490 --> 00:19:36,330
Thanks.

331
00:20:04,961 --> 00:20:07,598
You did a really great thing today.

332
00:20:08,450 --> 00:20:10,390
Thank you for the interview.

333
00:20:12,800 --> 00:20:13,650
Sure.

334
00:20:14,520 --> 00:20:15,530
It's been a long time.

335
00:20:16,690 --> 00:20:17,530
Yes.

336
00:20:17,640 --> 00:20:21,290
We met in front of the TV
station recently, didn't we?

337
00:20:22,050 --> 00:20:23,400
I wasn't sure at first...

338
00:20:24,020 --> 00:20:24,870
but it was you.

339
00:20:26,680 --> 00:20:28,410
We met long before last week.

340
00:20:29,900 --> 00:20:33,730
I believe you were behind the camera
of an interview I did 13 years ago.

341
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:35,530
Don't you remember?

342
00:20:36,330 --> 00:20:38,320
Mr Lee Joo-ho?

343
00:20:42,160 --> 00:20:43,000
I'm not sure.

344
00:20:43,660 --> 00:20:44,790
I don't really remember...

345
00:20:45,190 --> 00:20:46,900
I remember you very clearly.

346
00:20:47,970 --> 00:20:50,490
You were with Reporter Song Cha-ok
at that time, right?

347
00:20:55,550 --> 00:20:57,270
Choi In-ha, was her name?

348
00:20:58,060 --> 00:21:00,030
The woman that just interviewed me...

349
00:21:03,060 --> 00:21:04,260
is her daughter, isn't she?

350
00:21:07,160 --> 00:21:08,180
How interesting.

351
00:21:09,370 --> 00:21:10,400
I can't believe...

352
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:13,290
I met Reporter Song's daughter
through this accident.

353
00:21:13,800 --> 00:21:15,040
I find it very interesting...

354
00:21:18,640 --> 00:21:19,615
and grateful.

355
00:21:25,770 --> 00:21:27,380
By the way, you’re not doing this...

356
00:21:28,030 --> 00:21:29,990
to steal my exclusive news, are you?

357
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:34,092
-Hey!
-I mean, if that's the case...

358
00:21:35,960 --> 00:21:37,180
No, it's not like that.

359
00:21:39,260 --> 00:21:40,200
It's alright, then.

360
00:21:41,520 --> 00:21:43,430
Let's go back inside.
My senior must be waiting.

361
00:21:43,830 --> 00:21:44,670
Okay.

362
00:21:47,870 --> 00:21:49,154
One more thing, Dal-Po.

363
00:21:53,510 --> 00:21:55,710
Once we go back home
after the training period is over,

364
00:21:56,220 --> 00:21:57,910
my dad will find out about us.

365
00:22:00,380 --> 00:22:01,220
I know.

366
00:22:01,560 --> 00:22:03,890
It's possible that my dad
may act mean toward you.

367
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:05,790
I know.

368
00:22:05,880 --> 00:22:08,100
Even if he does, don't give up on us.

369
00:22:08,660 --> 00:22:09,680
I'll talk to my dad...

370
00:22:12,320 --> 00:22:13,170
I'd never do that.

371
00:22:28,740 --> 00:22:29,590
Seo Bum-Jo!

372
00:22:30,950 --> 00:22:32,160
I saw your report.

373
00:22:32,320 --> 00:22:33,200
You were great.

374
00:22:33,820 --> 00:22:34,700
I'm sorry.

375
00:22:34,910 --> 00:22:37,190
-It should've been you.
-Of course you should be sorry.

376
00:22:37,480 --> 00:22:39,710
I almost cursed on you,
but I hold it since it's you.

377
00:22:40,230 --> 00:22:41,070
Congratulations!

378
00:22:43,220 --> 00:22:44,060
Okay.

379
00:22:44,630 --> 00:22:47,000
You did a real great job today,
Seo Bum-Jo.

380
00:22:47,090 --> 00:22:47,940
Let's go!

381
00:23:08,220 --> 00:23:10,170
I heard you two were behind
the exclusive tonight?

382
00:23:10,260 --> 00:23:11,100
-Yes.
-Yes.

383
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:13,840
Good job.

384
00:23:19,410 --> 00:23:20,210
What?

385
00:23:20,300 --> 00:23:21,110
What are you doing?

386
00:23:21,200 --> 00:23:22,760
What did you just say?

387
00:23:24,480 --> 00:23:25,330
I said, good job.

388
00:23:26,060 --> 00:23:27,520
I can't hear you. Say it louder.

389
00:23:27,750 --> 00:23:29,570
I said, good job. Happy, now?

390
00:23:31,420 --> 00:23:32,750
Yes, I'm happy.

391
00:23:35,270 --> 00:23:36,750
How about removing that foot now?

392
00:23:37,590 --> 00:23:38,430
Sure.

393
00:23:40,730 --> 00:23:41,672
That shoes...

394
00:23:41,763 --> 00:23:43,500
Are they the right fit?

395
00:23:43,890 --> 00:23:44,730
Excuse me?

396
00:23:45,030 --> 00:23:46,240
Wait, Chief...!

397
00:23:50,700 --> 00:23:52,170
-Did you hear that?
-Yeah.

398
00:23:53,010 --> 00:23:54,646
Did Chief buy you those shoes?

399
00:23:54,737 --> 00:23:55,777
I guess so.

400
00:23:57,270 --> 00:24:00,050
I thought my dad bought this for me,
but it was my mom?

401
00:24:00,170 --> 00:24:01,100
Seriously?

402
00:24:01,400 --> 00:24:03,680
I had no idea! I can't believe it!

403
00:24:03,770 --> 00:24:04,790
No wonder!

404
00:24:04,880 --> 00:24:07,330
My dad wouldn't have the sense
to buy these kind of thing!

405
00:24:07,420 --> 00:24:09,170
I can't believe it!

406
00:24:09,260 --> 00:24:11,770
-Are you that happy?
-Of course, I'm happy!

407
00:24:12,120 --> 00:24:13,170
High-five!

408
00:24:15,560 --> 00:24:17,637
Hey, you have to lift up your right hand!

409
00:24:19,150 --> 00:24:19,990
Is it?

410
00:24:47,620 --> 00:24:50,030
Chief Song idea was right.

411
00:24:50,910 --> 00:24:52,890
Now that the ratings have been flipped,

412
00:24:53,160 --> 00:24:56,010
let's keep up the momentum
and go even bigger!

413
00:24:56,530 --> 00:25:00,063
I've prepared a private interview
with the driver of water delivery truck.

414
00:25:00,330 --> 00:25:02,350
How about making it
as our third item today?

415
00:25:02,630 --> 00:25:03,470
It sounds good.

416
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:04,520
Culture Chief.

417
00:25:04,950 --> 00:25:07,350
Create a story around the concept
of 'Heroes Amongst Us'...

418
00:25:07,440 --> 00:25:08,630
-by tomorrow.
-Yes.

419
00:25:08,720 --> 00:25:09,600
International Chief.

420
00:25:09,880 --> 00:25:11,730
Find out if there are
any similar foreign stories.

421
00:25:11,820 --> 00:25:14,560
We can't make a truck accident
as an exclusive news.

422
00:25:14,650 --> 00:25:16,580
They just got lucky with the story.

423
00:25:16,730 --> 00:25:18,620
Let's not distress our trainees
over it too much.

424
00:25:18,710 --> 00:25:21,409
But we still need to do
follow-up coverage.

425
00:25:21,850 --> 00:25:23,808
I heard that MSC even
has a private interview

426
00:25:23,899 --> 00:25:25,000
with the water deliveryman.

427
00:25:25,130 --> 00:25:28,718
This is no time for us to blame it
on luck when the ratings show otherwise.

428
00:25:30,520 --> 00:25:31,460
You're right...

429
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:34,170
This is no time for us
to be blaming it on luck.

430
00:25:34,580 --> 00:25:36,400
Not when the ratings have been flipped.

431
00:25:36,990 --> 00:25:39,400
Then, shall we go after the coverage?

432
00:25:40,650 --> 00:25:41,500
Don't do it.

433
00:25:41,620 --> 00:25:43,470
Come on, Mr Director!

434
00:25:44,500 --> 00:25:46,808
We need to report
the U.S. Vice President visit,

435
00:25:46,899 --> 00:25:48,431
asylum of North Korea's senior official,

436
00:25:48,522 --> 00:25:52,782
and even an in-depth report
of the Korea Australia FTA.

437
00:25:53,540 --> 00:25:54,740
That touching stories...

438
00:25:54,830 --> 00:25:57,439
is going to lose its heat
within the next couple of days.

439
00:25:57,529 --> 00:26:00,103
So, let's stop worrying about it,
and do what we should, okay?

440
00:26:04,229 --> 00:26:06,826
But the news of my brother didn't end
within the next couple of days.

441
00:26:07,149 --> 00:26:10,799
Mr Ki Jae-myung who risked his own life
to save the life of a boy yesterday...

442
00:26:10,889 --> 00:26:11,958
It didn't lose any heat

443
00:26:13,519 --> 00:26:14,629
but it flamed even hotter.

444
00:26:14,719 --> 00:26:17,269
When asked why he risked his own
life to save the life of the boy,

445
00:26:17,359 --> 00:26:19,459
he shared an unexpected
tragic story with us.

446
00:26:19,689 --> 00:26:21,849
Reporter Lee Il-joo brings
you the exclusive report.

447
00:26:22,809 --> 00:26:25,299
Mr Ki Jae-myung, who risked his
own life to save a student,

448
00:26:25,659 --> 00:26:28,639
loses his consciousness after calling out

449
00:26:28,749 --> 00:26:31,389
an unknown name at the
scene of the accident.

450
00:26:31,799 --> 00:26:32,729
Mister!

451
00:26:32,969 --> 00:26:37,009
The name Ha-myung turned out to be
the name of Mr Ki's late little brother.

452
00:26:37,479 --> 00:26:38,319
Yes.

453
00:26:39,229 --> 00:26:41,439
My little brother died right
around that same age.

454
00:26:42,139 --> 00:26:44,019
I must've rescued him
without even realizing it

455
00:26:44,509 --> 00:26:45,999
because he reminded me of him.

456
00:26:47,599 --> 00:26:50,269
They decided to just run
with a melodrama.

457
00:26:50,849 --> 00:26:52,011
Must we just sit back like this?

458
00:26:52,289 --> 00:26:53,319
We don’t have anything?

459
00:26:54,159 --> 00:26:56,525
Haven't you guys found
anything on Ki Jae-myung?

460
00:27:03,779 --> 00:27:04,746
Let's not get swept up in it.

461
00:27:05,369 --> 00:27:07,189
We don't need to jump into this hero game

462
00:27:07,279 --> 00:27:08,999
that we didn't even know anything about.

463
00:27:09,289 --> 00:27:12,319
That's why I'm asking you
to find that out. Got it?

464
00:27:13,729 --> 00:27:14,569
Yes, Sir.

465
00:27:15,629 --> 00:27:16,479
Choi Dal-Po.

466
00:27:18,519 --> 00:27:20,189
Forget about everything else,

467
00:27:20,819 --> 00:27:21,739
and focus on Ki Jae-myung.

468
00:27:21,829 --> 00:27:23,279
Report everything directly to me.

469
00:27:23,969 --> 00:27:24,809
Yes, Sir.

470
00:27:25,829 --> 00:27:26,492
Captain.

471
00:27:27,539 --> 00:27:28,999
Should I dig on Ki Jae-myung, too?

472
00:27:29,279 --> 00:27:30,339
Stay out of it.

473
00:27:31,139 --> 00:27:31,979
Yes, Sir.

474
00:27:34,259 --> 00:27:35,269
At the time...

475
00:27:35,989 --> 00:27:38,599
my father was slandered to have driven
nine of his fellow firemen to death

476
00:27:38,849 --> 00:27:40,899
and fled like a coward.

477
00:27:43,329 --> 00:27:45,189
But my father did not flee to escape.

478
00:27:46,469 --> 00:27:48,139
Even though he lost
his life in the fire...

479
00:27:48,769 --> 00:27:50,099
his body was never found.

480
00:27:52,499 --> 00:27:53,509
And recently...

481
00:27:55,929 --> 00:27:57,499
Thus, my brother became a hero.

482
00:27:59,119 --> 00:28:00,249
As a new-found hero,

483
00:28:00,859 --> 00:28:03,121
he tells the world of the
injustice done to our father.

484
00:28:03,539 --> 00:28:05,519
...my father's skeletal
remains were discovered.

485
00:28:05,859 --> 00:28:07,089
And he finally received...

486
00:28:07,749 --> 00:28:10,159
an apology that he so desperately longed
to hear 13 years ago.

487
00:28:10,249 --> 00:28:11,649
When the power of the media speaks,

488
00:28:11,739 --> 00:28:14,419
it is said that the pen
is mightier than the sword.

489
00:28:15,219 --> 00:28:17,001
It means, as the pen is
mightier than the sword,

490
00:28:17,229 --> 00:28:19,739
a pen can inflict a far
greater wound than a knife.

491
00:28:20,069 --> 00:28:23,259
In a show of assuming the responsibility
of the pain inflicted on Mr Ki Jae-myung,

492
00:28:23,349 --> 00:28:27,909
MSC News would like to extend
our most sincerest apology.

493
00:28:28,839 --> 00:28:30,899
We will also make you a promise.

494
00:28:31,509 --> 00:28:33,399
Just like how we, MSC News,

495
00:28:33,739 --> 00:28:36,349
bring you the exclusive
on Mr Ki Jae-myung's story of injustice,

496
00:28:36,439 --> 00:28:39,389
MSC will continue to strive
to report only the truth.

497
00:28:39,499 --> 00:28:41,769
We will do the role of a pen
properly and faithfully...

498
00:28:41,859 --> 00:28:42,949
The same news...

499
00:28:43,899 --> 00:28:46,119
that made my father
as an evil 13 years ago...

500
00:28:46,899 --> 00:28:49,859
now making my brother as a hero.

501
00:28:50,129 --> 00:28:52,409
I heard that Ki Jae-myung...

502
00:28:52,889 --> 00:28:55,054
was arrested by police
for violence during high school.

503
00:28:55,199 --> 00:28:57,409
That's not uncommon at that age.

504
00:28:58,279 --> 00:29:01,309
Ki Jae-myung is the lifeline
to our viewers ratings right now,

505
00:29:01,559 --> 00:29:03,691
Let's just pass on that and stay
with the touching stories.

506
00:29:04,619 --> 00:29:06,331
The news kept the darker
side of my brother

507
00:29:06,422 --> 00:29:07,673
hidden away from the world.

508
00:29:07,764 --> 00:29:10,551
Mr Ki is said to have come by here
every night on his way home

509
00:29:10,642 --> 00:29:12,839
to buy all kimbap left
from this grandmother.

510
00:29:13,509 --> 00:29:16,884
He'd buy all the leftover kimbap to help
her make ends in this cold weather...

511
00:29:16,975 --> 00:29:19,644
My brother's hidden good deeds
were made known to the world.

512
00:29:20,239 --> 00:29:23,419
Mr Ki took the reward of 500 dollars
from Han River Police Station

513
00:29:23,509 --> 00:29:25,107
and used it to buy Christmas gifts

514
00:29:25,198 --> 00:29:27,499
for the children
at a local children's shelter.

515
00:29:28,109 --> 00:29:30,660
Even his smallest good deeds
were praised by the world.

516
00:29:32,649 --> 00:29:34,579
Everything he did and said...

517
00:29:35,639 --> 00:29:38,775
like the Pied Piper from the fairytale
who left the children under his trance,

518
00:29:40,419 --> 00:29:42,069
starts to captivate the world.

519
00:29:54,689 --> 00:29:56,599
It's too crowded.
Let's take the next one.

520
00:29:57,079 --> 00:29:58,099
We may be able to fit.

521
00:30:00,429 --> 00:30:01,279
Hey, hey!

522
00:30:01,429 --> 00:30:02,809
It's already full please.

523
00:30:04,379 --> 00:30:05,929
-Hello.
