Why do you think that kind of father
is still on the run?

786
00:47:15,083 --> 00:47:16,013
My father...

787
00:47:18,903 --> 00:47:20,323
died with his boots on.

788
00:47:21,323 --> 00:47:22,373
What do you mean by that?

789
00:47:22,463 --> 00:47:24,886
A Pinocchio witness even stated
that he saw your father.

790
00:47:24,977 --> 00:47:26,929
I believe in my father
more than I do in a Pinocchio!

791
00:47:27,501 --> 00:47:29,519
That Pinocchio must've been mistaken.

792
00:47:29,621 --> 00:47:30,461
Wait.

793
00:47:30,561 --> 00:47:32,011
Hey, we're not here to listen to...

794
00:47:32,101 --> 00:47:34,071
I wish my father was alive, as well!

795
00:47:37,871 --> 00:47:41,972
What son in this world
would wish for their father to be dead?

796
00:47:42,801 --> 00:47:44,971
I don't care if people point
and call him a coward.

797
00:47:45,061 --> 00:47:48,031
I don't care if I never see him
as long as he's still alive!

798
00:47:50,191 --> 00:47:52,714
But the fact is,
that's not the type of a man he is.

799
00:47:54,651 --> 00:47:57,131
He's not the type of man
to leave his co-worker behind.

800
00:47:57,851 --> 00:48:00,831
He's not even more a man who'd abandon
his family and hiding somewhere.

801
00:48:02,741 --> 00:48:04,057
As a son...

802
00:48:06,061 --> 00:48:09,151
I hate to come into conclusion
of my father's death.

803
00:48:12,471 --> 00:48:13,961
But I know since I'm his son...

804
00:48:15,551 --> 00:48:16,421
My father...

805
00:48:19,341 --> 00:48:20,581
...died with his boots on.

806
00:48:23,381 --> 00:48:25,281
That's enough. We'll end it here.

807
00:48:32,721 --> 00:48:34,146
Why did you show this to me?

808
00:48:35,693 --> 00:48:36,641
The day we filmed this...

809
00:48:37,640 --> 00:48:38,930
there was one more incident.

810
00:48:40,530 --> 00:48:41,700
What incident?

811
00:48:47,180 --> 00:48:49,490
What do you think?
Was the interview newsworthy?

812
00:48:49,770 --> 00:48:53,110
Yeah, we can just use the part of him
yelling about only wanting his father

813
00:48:53,200 --> 00:48:54,730
to be alive even he's blamed.

814
00:48:55,750 --> 00:48:56,670
Wait, Seonbae.

815
00:48:57,410 --> 00:48:58,840
I think that's going too far.

816
00:48:58,930 --> 00:49:00,420
That wasn't the point of the interview.

817
00:49:00,510 --> 00:49:01,890
That was the point of it to me.

818
00:49:02,310 --> 00:49:04,069
The son is just as shameless
as his father is.

819
00:49:08,100 --> 00:49:09,240
Seonbae...

820
00:49:10,830 --> 00:49:12,300
You're not even a reporter.

821
00:49:12,580 --> 00:49:13,940
You're a monster!

822
00:49:14,030 --> 00:49:15,340
Let go! Let go of her!

823
00:49:15,550 --> 00:49:16,440
Seriously.

824
00:49:16,620 --> 00:49:17,930
We need some help over here!

825
00:49:45,200 --> 00:49:46,710
Seonbae, you should've tolerated him.

826
00:49:46,900 --> 00:49:48,440
It was a mistake stemming from anger.

827
00:49:48,760 --> 00:49:49,600
Mistake?

828
00:49:50,110 --> 00:49:51,830
He was going to hit me with that trophy.

829
00:49:52,380 --> 00:49:53,800
That was a clear attempted murder.

830
00:49:55,540 --> 00:49:57,910
He just hit the wall,
then stopped himself.

831
00:49:58,750 --> 00:49:59,750
Let's just settle this.

832
00:50:00,090 --> 00:50:02,820
If you just send him away like that,
he won't be able to go home...

833
00:50:02,910 --> 00:50:05,240
and he'll have to spend
the night in a cold holding cell.

834
00:50:05,330 --> 00:50:06,220
Good.

835
00:50:07,280 --> 00:50:08,420
That's what I want.

836
00:50:10,910 --> 00:50:11,990
Because of that incident,

837
00:50:12,290 --> 00:50:14,420
Ki Jae-myung wasn't able
to go home that night.

838
00:50:15,880 --> 00:50:16,720
And later that night,

839
00:50:17,330 --> 00:50:19,240
Ki Jae-myung's mother
and his little brother...

840
00:50:20,030 --> 00:50:21,944
jumped off a cliff
and committed dual suicide.

841
00:50:22,860 --> 00:50:25,631
Ki Jae-myung believes that
if he gone home that night,

842
00:50:25,722 --> 00:50:28,080
he can stop that tragedy from happening.

843
00:50:29,190 --> 00:50:30,030
That's why...

844
00:50:30,490 --> 00:50:32,920
he has a huge resentment
against Chief Song.

845
00:50:38,880 --> 00:50:39,720
Is my mom...

846
00:50:41,260 --> 00:50:42,220
aware of all this?

847
00:50:43,080 --> 00:50:43,920
Yeah.

848
00:50:49,460 --> 00:50:50,930
Revive them, you bastards!

849
00:50:51,120 --> 00:50:52,100
You guys killed them.

850
00:50:52,190 --> 00:50:55,010
You guys killed
my little brother and my mother!

851
00:50:55,860 --> 00:50:59,145
You guys killed them
with the words you spread.

852
00:51:00,920 --> 00:51:02,832
Get a shot of the shoe
with the sea in the background.

853
00:51:06,680 --> 00:51:07,721
This is your fault!

854
00:51:08,200 --> 00:51:11,710
This never would've happened,
if I was with my mother last night!

855
00:51:11,800 --> 00:51:12,630
No.

856
00:51:12,720 --> 00:51:14,820
If you were with her last night,
you would've died together.

857
00:51:20,790 --> 00:51:21,930
I will kill you.

858
00:51:22,020 --> 00:51:24,180
I'm going to kill you!

859
00:51:31,960 --> 00:51:33,270
That guy, Ki Jae-myung...

860
00:51:34,140 --> 00:51:35,590
there's something fishy about him.

861
00:51:36,330 --> 00:51:37,687
The way he took that flier

862
00:51:37,778 --> 00:51:39,311
about Chief Song's upcoming
lecture that day...

863
00:51:39,740 --> 00:51:41,390
And I don't know if I'm too sensitive...

864
00:51:42,570 --> 00:51:44,848
But he seems to think
something dangerous.

865
00:51:46,260 --> 00:51:49,920
No matter how I warn her, she just won't
listen. She's still just going to do it.

866
00:51:50,320 --> 00:51:52,736
She said she'd prefer that he attacks her
out of his grudge.

867
00:51:52,827 --> 00:51:54,955
She welcomes the newsworthy attack!

868
00:51:56,140 --> 00:51:58,030
Anyhow, can you try to stop her?

869
00:51:58,320 --> 00:51:59,160
Who knows?

870
00:51:59,350 --> 00:52:00,930
Maybe she'll listen to her daughter.

871
00:52:05,290 --> 00:52:06,400
Are you even listening to me?

872
00:52:11,360 --> 00:52:12,422
Is my mom...

873
00:52:15,590 --> 00:52:17,970
I mean, Chief Song,
that cruel of a person?

874
00:52:20,290 --> 00:52:21,130
Choi In-ha.

875
00:52:21,460 --> 00:52:23,230
How could she do that?

876
00:52:23,380 --> 00:52:24,580
How come...?

877
00:52:32,550 --> 00:52:33,720
I really...

878
00:52:34,050 --> 00:52:35,740
I really can't understand it.

879
00:52:42,190 --> 00:52:43,060
That shoe...

880
00:52:44,640 --> 00:52:45,540
What is that shoe?

881
00:52:48,400 --> 00:52:49,260
This is...

882
00:52:49,380 --> 00:52:51,040
That shoe belonged
to Ki Jae-myung's brother.

883
00:52:51,130 --> 00:52:53,040
The one that drowned in the sea
with his mother.

884
00:52:54,660 --> 00:52:56,070
Ki Jae-myung's little brother?

885
00:52:56,630 --> 00:52:57,470
That's right.

886
00:52:58,890 --> 00:53:01,020
He told you that during the interview
at the hospital.

887
00:53:01,890 --> 00:53:03,910
Was it Ki... Ha-myung?

888
00:53:05,820 --> 00:53:07,220
That's his little brother's shoe.

889
00:53:15,520 --> 00:53:16,360
I'll be back.

890
00:53:22,680 --> 00:53:23,680
No way.

891
00:53:27,700 --> 00:53:28,490
Hey.

892
00:53:28,580 --> 00:53:29,420
Choi In-ha!

893
00:53:29,660 --> 00:53:30,510
Hey!

894
00:53:30,910 --> 00:53:32,010
Hey! Hey! Hey!

895
00:53:32,130 --> 00:53:33,270
Hey! Hey!

896
00:53:33,470 --> 00:53:34,600
Choi In-ha!

897
00:53:38,550 --> 00:53:39,390
Hey!

898
00:53:40,410 --> 00:53:41,250
Hey!

899
00:53:48,200 --> 00:53:50,310
It was either last September or October,

900
00:53:50,400 --> 00:53:52,010
the day a high sea warning issued.

901
00:53:52,100 --> 00:53:54,400
I took the boat out to sea by myself

902
00:53:54,490 --> 00:53:56,980
to fix the pole from the storm.

903
00:53:57,390 --> 00:54:01,970
That's when I saw
something cling to a pillar.

904
00:54:10,150 --> 00:54:10,990
Oh my.

905
00:54:11,150 --> 00:54:11,990
In-ha.

906
00:54:12,710 --> 00:54:14,931
What are you doing home at this hour?

907
00:54:18,500 --> 00:54:24,690
In-ha, I finally bought a television
to see you and Dal-Po on the news.

908
00:54:28,090 --> 00:54:29,010
Look at this.

909
00:54:29,100 --> 00:54:31,650
The colors and everything are so clear.

910
00:54:34,080 --> 00:54:35,400
-Grandfather.
-Huh?

911
00:54:36,600 --> 00:54:39,090
This shoe... What is this shoe?

912
00:54:41,180 --> 00:54:42,460
Hey, you can't throw that out!

913
00:54:42,550 --> 00:54:43,990
That's the shoe...

914
00:54:44,690 --> 00:54:46,340
that saved your uncle's life

915
00:54:46,430 --> 00:54:48,990
when it got caught in
the pillar back then.

916
00:54:49,305 --> 00:54:52,040
That shoe is like a talisman.

917
00:54:57,550 --> 00:54:58,390
By the way...

918
00:54:59,730 --> 00:55:01,290
did you two make an appointment today?

919
00:55:02,230 --> 00:55:05,410
I thought you guys couldn't come home
because of that mawari or something.

920
00:55:06,010 --> 00:55:07,689
How did you both manage
to come home today?

921
00:55:08,320 --> 00:55:09,730
Uncle came by the house?

922
00:55:09,860 --> 00:55:10,700
Yeah.

923
00:55:11,070 --> 00:55:11,980
Come here.

924
00:55:13,220 --> 00:55:15,410
I think something's going on with Dal-Po.

925
00:55:16,340 --> 00:55:19,298
I don't know what's
happened, but he just...

926
00:55:19,950 --> 00:55:23,920
walked around the house
then went up to the rooftop.

927
00:55:28,210 --> 00:55:29,050
In-ha.

928
00:55:29,310 --> 00:55:30,800
Are you leaving again now?

929
00:55:43,290 --> 00:55:44,410
Let me ask you something.

930
00:55:44,850 --> 00:55:46,060
Why do you hate me?

931
00:55:46,400 --> 00:55:49,020
Am I your sworn enemy or something?

932
00:55:49,320 --> 00:55:50,900
Of course you're my sworn enemy.

933
00:55:51,020 --> 00:55:52,420
I'm not going to be disappointed.

934
00:55:53,030 --> 00:55:56,260
No matter how badly you and my dad slander
my mom, I won't believe any of it.

935
00:55:56,810 --> 00:55:58,230
It's not slander, but the truth.

936
00:56:04,560 --> 00:56:06,810
They should be careful, and more careful!

937
00:56:07,140 --> 00:56:09,100
Being not aware of that is their fault!

938
00:56:13,800 --> 00:56:14,940
That negligence...

939
00:56:15,950 --> 00:56:17,430
has destroyed a family.

940
00:56:18,760 --> 00:56:20,990
That's why they must take responsibility
for it.

941
00:56:23,290 --> 00:56:24,180
I think...

942
00:56:24,940 --> 00:56:26,590
that you shouldn't be a reporter.

943
00:56:27,790 --> 00:56:28,640
I mean that.

944
00:56:33,430 --> 00:56:35,420
Tell me, was that all just a lie?

945
00:56:41,120 --> 00:56:41,960
Hey!

946
00:56:42,350 --> 00:56:43,580
You crazy bastard!

947
00:56:48,330 --> 00:56:49,170
Dal-Po.

948
00:56:50,590 --> 00:56:51,530
Dal-Po.

949
00:57:11,050 --> 00:57:12,560
Please don't get involved with him.

950
00:57:12,990 --> 00:57:14,740
Don't ask me for reasons. Just please...

951
00:57:16,130 --> 00:57:17,720
Please don't, okay?

952
00:57:36,270 --> 00:57:37,170
In-ha.

953
00:58:01,890 --> 00:58:02,930
Are you by any chance...

954
00:58:07,700 --> 00:58:08,740
Ki Ha-myung?

955
00:58:19,410 --> 00:58:20,260
Are you?

956
00:58:22,630 --> 00:58:24,210
Is your real name...

957
00:58:27,300 --> 00:58:28,490
Ki Ha-myung?

958
00:58:32,590 --> 00:58:33,430
How did you...?

959
00:58:34,380 --> 00:58:35,260
How did you find...?

960
00:58:48,910 --> 00:58:50,344
The truth that I've wanted
to keep hidden...

961
00:58:51,770 --> 00:58:54,100
was found out by the person
who should've never known it.

962
00:59:13,610 --> 00:59:14,860
Did you return the pin recorder?

963
00:59:14,950 --> 00:59:16,730
-Let me return it.
-So, you've made your decision.

964
00:59:16,820 --> 00:59:17,940
-Captain.
-Choi Dal-Po

965
00:59:18,200 --> 00:59:19,250
I'll dig around Ki Jae-myung.

966
00:59:19,340 --> 00:59:22,080
Tell me who your real family is,
then I'll reconsider it.

967
00:59:22,930 --> 00:59:24,635
He makes In-ha laugh and cry...

968
00:59:24,726 --> 00:59:26,379
-My In-ha?
-You don't know?

969
00:59:26,470 --> 00:59:27,304
You said you didn't know?

970
00:59:28,100 --> 00:59:29,640
I think I may be gone for a while.

971
00:59:29,731 --> 00:59:31,621
-Where?
-Somewhere far...

972
00:59:31,712 --> 00:59:33,375
Ki Jae-myung's wrath is justified.

973
00:59:33,710 --> 00:59:35,810
Why did you do it?
Even I was able to endure it.

974
00:59:35,960 --> 00:59:37,420
Because it seems you hold it back.

975
00:59:39,030 --> 00:59:40,010
Are you okay?
